<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Sponsors</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
We will not consider any player that approaches us without sponsors. Like many in the guild, I don’t do much grouping outside the guild and my small circle of friends. As such, I don’t get many opportunities to meet and hunt with recruits. I tend to look toward my fellow guild mates that may have history with a recruit and will vouch for them. Any attempts to recruit with us without securing sponsors first will be ignored.<br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Message Board and Website</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Visiting these boards is an excellent step in the right direction. The message board is the hub of all communication for the guild. We can’t force people to read the message board, but we certainly expect it. Information is power, and you’ll find a lot of it here. We strategize, we debate, we plan, we do it all on these message boards. If you can’t keep up with the posts, you’ll be out of loop and out of luck. It might sound like a lot, but a few minutes on the boards before you log on every night goes a long way. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Levels</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The bulk of our guild is level 60 or higher. This makes it especially hard for lower level recruits to make an impression. A lot of us have twinks, but we either play them very rarely or we level them so fast it’s hard to keep up with us. If you are low level, you will find it is difficult getting opportunities to meet and hunt with us. And if you do get invited, be prepared to be on the outside looking in for awhile as a low level member.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>We are not an UberGuild</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This is not an uberguild. We don’t aspire to be one. We like beating the odds and trying new things. One week we might raid a lot, but then we might go 3 weeks without raiding at all. Some raids are planned; others are spur of the moment. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>We are not a stepping stone guild</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This isn’t a guild you join to get your epic, level 60, some AAXP, and then leave to join an uberguild. This is should be the last guild you ever join. We are tight knit group and put a lot of trust in each other. We need to be sure each and every one of us will always be there for each and contribute to the continuing growth of the guild. We have our ups and downs and I expect that you can handle them. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Competence</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
You should know how to play your class. You should know how to raid. You should know how to use loc or the cartography system. You should know EQ. As a guild we don’t require members to prove their skill level in the game. But as someone that might have to group with you and raid with you one day, I expect you know what you are doing. You’ll find that we can be one of the most helpful players you’ll meet, but we don’t always have the time to walk you through something. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Maturity</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
We can be sarcastic, we can witty, but all our members, young and old, are mature. While there may be the occasional obscenity over guildchat, lewd remarks are not the norm. We don’t argue over public channels or call people names. We have real life husbands and wives, boyfriends and girlfriends, and parents and children in this guild. We are always mindful of our words and try not to offend.<br>
